<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[192,1440,1187,1436]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,317,1187,1211]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Remarks</emphasis>
. An unusually colored species, 
<taxonomicName box="[705,862,1187,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pectoralis">
<emphasis box="[705,727,1188,1211]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[742,862,1187,1211]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">pectoralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will not go beyond couplet 
<quantity box="[1199,1246,1187,1211]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
the species key (
<bibRefCitation author="Gordon, R. D. &amp; C. Canepari" box="[200,521,1219,1243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" pagination="245 - 512" refId="ref7630" refString="Gordon, R. D., and C. Canepari. 2008. South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part XI: a systematic revision of Hyperaspidini (Hyperaspidinae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; XCIX: 245 - 512." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gordon and Canepari 2008</bibRefCitation>
) because it has no dorsal color pattern. It is described as being dorsally yellow, but this is a “dirty” yellow because the bottom of the punctures are distinctly or faintly brown. Male genitalia place it in the onerata group, but the round, convex body form differs from other species in that group.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[192,1440,1187,1436]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">
The type specimen is a 
<typeStatus box="[515,618,1347,1371]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">holotype</typeStatus>
male in the Crotch collection (UMZC). This species was omitted from the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[237,373,1380,1403]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Hyperaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[237,373,1380,1403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Hyperaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
revision (
<bibRefCitation author="Gordon, R. D. &amp; C. Canepari" box="[487,810,1379,1403]" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" pagination="245 - 512" refId="ref7630" refString="Gordon, R. D., and C. Canepari. 2008. South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part XI: a systematic revision of Hyperaspidini (Hyperaspidinae). Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale &quot; G. Doria &quot; XCIX: 245 - 512." type="book chapter" year="2008">Gordon and Canepari 2008</bibRefCitation>
) because it was mistakenly identified as a member of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[237,437,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Brachiacanthini">Brachiacanthini</taxonomicName>
genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant." authorityName="Mulsant." box="[520,696,1411,1435]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Cyra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[520,580,1412,1435]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="9">Cyra</emphasis>
Mulsant.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
